articles.author: Express News Service
articles.title: Shooting: India set for record representation at Paris Olympics after Varun Tomar, Esha Singh take quota tally to 15 - The Indian Express
articles.description: India record gold-silver finish in men’s 10m air pistol event as Tomar edges out Arjun Singh Cheema in the final of the Asian Olympic qualifiers; Esha Singh wins gold medal in women’s 10m air pistol event.
articles.content: Varun Tomar, the younger cousin of former world champion and Tokyo Olympian Saurabh Chaudhary, and teenage shooter Esha Singh won Indias 14th and 15th quota respectively for this years Paris Games. B… [+2724 chars]
